        <mxCell id="Fxhjtc0vtD10ZX0brtwV-37" value="&lt;div style=&quot;line-height: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Merits:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- merits are some kind of currency/token&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- merits are used to buy favours or upgrades&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- you start a run with a couple of merits or use them to buy upgrades before game&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- you carry them around as token&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- only very few NPC steal them&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- whenever you faint/trapped you loose some of your upgrades unless they are permanent&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- therefore spending all your merits on upgrades at game start might not be your best choice&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- there are small/med/grand merits; you can convert: up 4:1 but down 1:3&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;- merits are earned by sidequests or found in chests&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;spacing=5;spacingTop=-20;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;fillColor=#f5f5f5;strokeColor=#666666;fontColor=#333333;expand=1;collapsible=1;" parent="1" vertex="1">
